I targeted the next boundary that the latest native run still misses most cleanly: static definition/explanation prompts drifting into `TOOL_NEEDED`. The benchmark errors included `DIRECT_ANSWER -> TOOL_NEEDED` on prompts like “What are needs versus wants?”, “What does opportunity cost mean?”, and “What is a short-term goal?”, so I added one small train-only contrast pack with 5 static-knowledge `DIRECT_ANSWER` examples and 3 similarly phrased live/current `TOOL_NEEDED` examples, then rebuilt `train_sft.jsonl` through the existing extra-train merge path. That keeps the experiment narrow and comparable while directly addressing the current weak boundary.

